null, "body": "Older tests tend to use testrepo as if they were DataLad datasets. However, I keep forgetting that they are not, as they are generated without DataLad tooling and make no attempt to even look like actual datasets. Symptoms:\r\n\r\n1. They do not have a dataset ID\r\n2. They do not carry the default gitattriutes\r\n    ```\r\n    * annex.backend=MD5E\r\n    **/.git* annex.largefiles=nothing\r\n    ``` \r\n\r\nNow one could argue whether this is a bug or a feature, but in the concrete case of adding a subdataset to a non-dataset, `.gitmodules` ends up being annexed -- which is a problem.\r\nGitRepo.add_submodule() is not committing this change so various places need a fix, but I am not yet sure which approach is best.\r\n\r\nA symptom of this problem as the failing tests in                      https://github.com/datalad/datalad/pull/3304: e.g. https://travis-ci.org/datalad/datalad/jobs/517362633#L1781               ", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3306/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused